                            <comment id="14015177" author="mishail" created="Mon, 2 Jun 2014 05:06:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to use a message from IllegalArgumentException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem exists only in 1.2/2.0.x and was fixed in 2.1 by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7189&quot; title=&quot;Repair hang when specified CF does not exist&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7189&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7189&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14016985" author="mishail" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 18:50:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yukim&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yukim&quot;&gt;yukim&lt;/a&gt; could you please review?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14016995" author="nickmbailey" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 18:58:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there a way to get this to propagate to the synchronous jmx api as well?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14017147" author="yukim" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 21:04:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on the patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nickmbailey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nickmbailey&quot;&gt;nickmbailey&lt;/a&gt; async and sync use the same Runnable task to run repair. So even with sync api, you can listen to JMX notification. Unfortunately, not able to propagate like throwing Exception.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14017169" author="mishail" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 21:18:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
